    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ensuring-equity-markets-support-long-term-growth-government-response-to-the-kay-review"/>
    <title>Ensuring equity markets support long-term growth: government response to the Kay review</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Government’s response to Professor John Kay’s report into the effect of UK equity markets on the competitiveness of UK business (URN 12/917). Explains why the Government accepts Professor Kay’s analysis and his suggested principles for UK equity markets, and the directions from these principles for market participants and regulatory policy makers. Also provides detailed responses to the 17 more specific review recommendations, explaining what steps the Government is taking to deliver these, and where they are engaging with business and investment industry stakeholders to encourage them to take the lead.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
